Personal Information We Collect
We may collect Personal Information about you from a variety of ways depending on how you interact with our restaurants, websites, or mobile services. This information includes:

Personal Identifiers such as name, address, phone number (including mobile), email address, and username and password to access Darden products and online services;
Other Personal Identifiers such as names, postal addresses, e-mail addresses, and telephone numbers of others to whom you ask us to send information;
Demographic Information such as date of birth, marital status, family structures, educational levels, employment status, household income and dwelling, and characteristics of protected classifications under state or federal law, such as gender, race, and military status;
Financial Information such as payment card details, financial account information, billing address, and home mortgage.
Internet/Network Information such as Internet Protocol (IP) Address and/or domain, internet service provider, internet click activity on our websites or mobile apps, analytics data, browsing history, and search history;
Commercial Information such as online order and reservation history, records of products or services purchased, obtained, or considered, or other purchasing or consuming histories or tendencies;
Geo-location information of your computer or mobile device, such as your city, state, province, and country. When you access the mobile app, we may collect precise geo-location information if you permit the app to access such information so that we may provide you with directions based on your location and proximity to the nearest Darden family restaurant;
Audio/Video information, such as CCTV images, photograph; and
Other Personal Information you may provide to us, such as comments, chats, opinions, and mobile carrier.

How We Collect Information
We may collect your Personal Information provided directly by you or a member of your household when you:

Create an account on one of our websites or mobile services;
Place an in-person or on-line to go order, or other transaction, with us;
Enable your Geolocation services;
Make a payment for products or services;
Participate in our eClub or any loyalty programs;
Make a reservation;
Purchase a Gift Card;
Participate in promotional sweepstakes;
Provide feedback or participate in a survey;
Contact us with a question or request; and
“Like,” “Follow” or otherwise connect with or post to one of our Social Media Pages.

How We Use Your Personal Information
We collect and use your Personal Information for the following purposes:

Create and manage your account;
Offer and provide products and services to you;
Process and collect payments for goods and services;
Communicate about, and administer your participation in special events, programs, rewards, surveys, contests, sweepstakes, and other offers or promotions;
For targeted advertising and marketing services;
Send information to others if you ask us to do so;
Respond to and communicate with you about your requests, concerns, questions, and comments;
Operate, evaluate, and improve our business;
Perform data analyses;
Protect against, identify, and prevent fraud and other criminal activity, claims, and other liabilities;
Collect location data to enable check-in notification for curbside to-go orders when you arrive at the restaurant, even when the app is closed or not in use; and
Comply with and enforce applicable legal requirements, relevant industry standards, and our policies.
We comply with and enforce applicable legal requirements, relevant industry standards, and our policies. For example, we may use the information you provide when you complete an online order, transaction, or reservation. When you sign up with our eClub or rewards and provide us with your contact information, we may also use that information to contact you with news and special offers.

To the extent permitted by applicable law and with your consent where required, we also use information collected through automated means for purposes such as (i) customizing our users’ visits to our site, (ii) delivering content (including advertising) tailored to our users’ interests and the manner in which our users browse our site, and (iii) managing our site and other aspects of our business. To the extent permitted by applicable law, we also may use this information to provide you with ads about our products when you browse this and other websites or use our mobile apps.

